{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 Liberation Sans;}{\f1 Liberation Mono;}}\paperw11906\paperh16838\margl1134\margr1134\margt1134\margb1134\f0\fs22\b THOG2 CURVE, SHEET, BLOCK, CHEBY, DCT Planning Spec\b0\par\par Purpose: planning spec for the staged compact-geometry and basis-family work in thog2. This is documentation only.\par\par\b Vocabulary\b0\par DENSE means conventional repeated transformer weights. It is not a basis family and should not be combined with CURVE, SHEET, or BLOCK.\par CHEBY means the current Chebyshev first-kind compact basis family.\par DCT means a real orthonormal DCT basis family, initially DCT-II, exposed to users simply as DCT.\par CURVE, SHEET, and BLOCK are compact geometry choices and should be selectable independently of CHEBY or DCT.\par Valid run identities are DENSE, CHEBY_CURVE, CHEBY_SHEET, CHEBY_BLOCK, DCT_CURVE, DCT_SHEET, and DCT_BLOCK.\par\par\b 1. Abstraction Refactor\b0\par\b Goal\b0\par Separate compact geometry, basis family, and transformer tensor-family metadata. Make CURVE a first-class compact geometry. Preserve current CHEBY_SHEET behaviour during the refactor.\par\par\b Target config surface\b0\par\f1 model_family = dense | compact\par compact_geometry = curve | sheet | block\par basis_family = chebyshev | dct\par\f0\par User-facing run tokens should remain DENSE, CHEBY, DCT, CURVE, SHEET, BLOCK.\par\par\b Geometry definitions\b0\par CURVE compacts transformer depth only. Matrix entries remain explicit over output row and input column.\par\f1 W_l[o,i] = sum_p C[o,i,p] * B_depth[l,p]\par\f0 SHEET compacts depth plus one matrix axis. The existing SHEET implementation compresses the input-column axis and leaves output rows explicit.\par\f1 W_l[o,i] = sum_pq C[o,p,q] * B_depth[l,p] * B_input[i,q]\par\f0 BLOCK compacts depth, output rows, and input columns.\par\f1 W_l[o,i] = sum_pqr C[p,q,r] * B_depth[l,p] * B_output[o,q] * B_input[i,r]\par\f0\par\b Module boundaries\b0\par basis.py should expose basis-family dispatch rather than directly building only Chebyshev bases. geometry.py should describe tensor-family axes and compact axes without assuming SHEET-only coefficient shapes. trajectory code should expose a stable materialize(name, layer_index) interface independent of CURVE, SHEET, BLOCK, CHEBY, or DCT. The transformer model path should continue to call materialize by semantic family name.\par\par\b Minimum abstractions\b0\par BasisSpec: sample_count, order, basis_family, basis_version, dtype, device.\par AxisSpec: semantic name, sample_count, order, optional derived-order policy.\par FamilySpec: semantic tensor family name, dense shape, compact axes, initialization policy, weight-decay policy.\par TrajectorySpec: compact_geometry, basis_family, depth_order, input_order/base_input_order, output_order/base_output_order where applicable.\par\par\b Compatibility requirements\b0\par Existing CHEBY_SHEET checkpoints must either load unchanged or fail clearly. Silent semantic reinterpretation is unacceptable. Checkpoint metadata must record compact_geometry, basis_family, basis_version, depth_order, and all non-depth order settings. Resume must hard-fail when basis_family or compact_geometry differs from the checkpoint. DENSE must remain a clean control path.\par\par\b Acceptance tests\b0\par Default CHEBY_SHEET parameter counts and materialized tensor shapes remain unchanged. Basis buffers remain non-persistent. Optimizer groups cover trainable parameters exactly once. CURVE materialization matches direct scalar evaluation. Checkpoint mismatch tests cover compact_geometry and basis_family.\par\par\b 2. BLOCK\b0\par\b Goal\b0\par Add the 3D compact geometry where rows and columns have separate basis expansions, while depth remains compact. Implement BLOCK as an option without breaking DENSE and SHEET paths.\par\par\b Matrix formula\b0\par\f1 W_l[o,i] = sum_pqr C[p,q,r] * D[l,p] * O[o,q] * I[i,r]\par\f0 D is depth basis. O is output-row basis. I is input-column basis. C is the compact coefficient block for one semantic tensor family.\par\par\b Vector and bias handling\b0\par Vectors do not have distinct output and input axes. For layernorm weights and biases, attention biases, and MLP biases, BLOCK should reduce to depth plus feature-axis compression. CURVE vectors should compact depth only and leave feature entries explicit. SHEET and BLOCK vectors can share depth plus feature-axis representation unless a later experiment requires a different policy.\par\par\b Order policy\b0\par Retain depth_order. Introduce input_order/base_input_order for input-column axes. Introduce output_order/base_output_order for output-row axes. Use explicit integer derived-order rules and record derived orders in the family report. Avoid hiding output-order scaling inside a name that says row_order.\par\par\b Implementation recommendation\b0\par Do not mutate SheetTrajectory directly as the first step. After the abstraction refactor, either add a sibling BlockTrajectory or a generalized CompactTrajectory with geometry-specific coefficient layout adapters. Use einsum or equivalent staged matrix products for clarity first; optimize after correctness and memory measurements are stable.\par\par\b Initialization and tests\b0\par Re-derive coefficient standard deviations for BLOCK so materialized dense weights hit intended target standard deviation. Do not assume the SHEET coefficient scale transfers unchanged. Tests must cover shapes, direct scalar evaluation, parameter reports, residual-init scaling, CPU train/save/resume, and GPU dtype/device movement.\par\par\b 3. DCT\b0\par\b Goal\b0\par Add DCT as a user-selectable alternative to CHEBY for CURVE, SHEET, and BLOCK. DENSE remains unaffected. The user-facing token should be DCT, not DCT2. Internally, record basis_version as dct_ii_orthonormal_v1.\par\par\b Recommended variant\b0\par Use orthonormal DCT-II first. Do not use complex FFT/DFT as the initial Fourier-like basis. Periodic wrap-around is a bad default prior for layer depth, rows, or columns unless explicitly tested later. DCT-II is real, orthonormal on a finite interval, and behaves as a smooth low-frequency basis without forcing cyclic adjacency.\par\par\b DCT-II basis\b0\par\f1 B[n,0] = sqrt(1 / N)\par B[n,k] = sqrt(2 / N) * cos(pi * (n + 0.5) * k / N), for k > 0\par Use columns k = 0 .. order-1\par\f0 N is sample_count for the axis. The basis should be orthonormal by construction; QR should not be required for DCT-II, but Gram-error tests must verify this.\par\par\b Migration safety\b0\par A CHEBY checkpoint must not resume under DCT, even if coefficient tensor shapes happen to match. A DCT checkpoint must not resume under CHEBY. Changing basis_family should require a fresh run unless a future conversion tool is added.\par\par\b Experiment plan\b0\par First compare CHEBY_CURVE vs DCT_CURVE. Then compare CHEBY_SHEET vs DCT_SHEET. Only after BLOCK correctness is stable, compare CHEBY_BLOCK vs DCT_BLOCK. Keep DENSE as the conventional control, not as part of the basis-family matrix.\par\par\b Implementation staging summary\b0\par Stage A: abstraction refactor with explicit CURVE and unchanged CHEBY_SHEET behaviour.\par Stage B: BLOCK with CHEBY only.\par Stage C: DCT basis option for CURVE, SHEET, and BLOCK.\par Do not combine BLOCK and DCT implementation in the same first-pass PR.\par}